# Extension Version Bump

Whenever you change any extension files (`content.js`, `background.js`, `popup.js`, `sidebar.css`, `popup.html`, `manifest.json`, etc.), **always bump `version` in `manifest.json`** in the same change.

- Use semver patch bumps by default (`1.2` → `1.3` → `1.4`)
- Do this even for small UI/CSS tweaks — it helps Chrome pick up reloads and avoid stale UI
- Mention the new version briefly when telling the user to reload the extension
